SIMPLE: purveyor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purveyor
<hw>Pur*vey"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>porveour</ets>, OF. <ets>pourveor</ets>, F. <ets>pourvoyeur</ets>.
See <er>Purvey</er>, and cf. <er>Proveditor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who provides victuals, or whose business is to make provision
for the table; a victualer; a caterer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An officer who formerly provided, or exacted
provision, for the king's household.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a procurer; a pimp; a bawd.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purview</ent>⟦br⟧
